<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1276" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1276">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9313.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Forced loan by the Federals is expected here. British Consul just now
                            called and we shall recommend foreigners refusing payment.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>